name: INAUGURAL TO LONDON - WestJet 767-338ER [C-FOGJ] Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
On May 6th 2016, WestJet started a new chapter in its history, launching three new routes to London's Gatwick airport, one from Toronto which will operate daily, one from Vancouver, which will operate 6x a week and one from Calgary (as seen here) which will operate 5x a week. Edmonton will receive flights 2x a week starting May 7th, as will Winnipeg 1x a week. Fittingly, Calgary's flight numbers are WS1 outbound and WS2 inbound, being the city that they started operations in 20 years ago, in addition to the flight being operated by their first 767. Enjoy the video of this special occasion!

Thanks for watching!

FLIGHT INFO
Airline: Westjet (WJA/WS)
Aircraft: Boeing 767-300ER/WL (B76W)
Aircraft Name: 671
Livery: Revised
Engines: 2x GE CF6-80c2b6
Registration: C-FOGJ
Route: YYC-LGW
Callsign: WestJet 1 heavy
Runway used: 17L
Local Time: 1900
